    <note>Tang(1) Dongye [1591] His ancestors had the surname Yin(1) and lived in Puzhou, Quancheng xian. During the disorder of the Five Dynasties, they fled south and changed their surname to Tang(1) because of taboo on homonyms with Taizu's mingzi, the same as Tang(1) Penju's [1590] ancestors so 2 branches of the same root lineage. His nephew Yinian's [3819] father-in-law was Zhou(1) Linzhi [8034]. Yinian's son, Yuan [3822], and Dongye's grandson, Yong [3821], both have the same generational name as Yi [1588]. Jiangxi TZ, 9.46b; Jingkou qi jiuzhuan, 5.1b; XNYL, 24.6b, 25.9b, 28.2a, 5a, 35.10a, 40.8b, 48.6a, 51.8b, 10a, 96.10b; SHY:ZG, 42.55a, 69.4a-4b, 5a; Liu Zai, WJ, 33.16b; Songshi yi, 7.11b. CBD, 4, 2777.</note>
